data.name: ArgumentIsEmpty
data.value: The string argument '{argumentName}' cannot be empty.

data.name: CircularDependency
data.value: A circular dependency was detected: {cycle}.

data.name: InvalidEnumValue
data.value: The value provided for argument '{argumentName}' must be a valid value of enum type '{enumType}'.

data.name: InvalidPropertiesExpression
data.value: The properties expression '{expression}' is not valid. The expression should represent a property access: 't => t.MyProperty'. When specifying multiple properties use an anonymous type: 't => new {{ t.MyProperty1, t.MyProperty2 }}'.

data.name: InvalidPropertyExpression
data.value: The expression '{expression}' is not a valid property expression. The expression should represent a property access: 't => t.MyProperty'.

data.name: IdentityConflict
data.value: The instance of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be tracked because another instance of this type with the same key is already being tracked. For new entities consider using an IIdentityGenerator to generate unique key values.

data.name: InvalidPrimaryKey
data.value: The instance of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be tracked because it has an invalid (e.g. null or CLR default) primary key. Either set the key explicitly or consider using an IValueGenerator to generate unique key values.

data.name: WrongStateManager
data.value: Cannot start tracking InternalEntityEntry for entity type '{entityType}' because it was created by a different StateManager instance.

data.name: MultipleEntries
data.value: Cannot start tracking InternalEntityEntry for entity type '{entityType}' because another InternalEntityEntry is already tracking the same entity.

data.name: PropertyNotFound
data.value: The property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' could not be found. Ensure that the property exists and has been included in the model.

data.name: CollectionArgumentIsEmpty
data.value: The collection argument '{argumentName}' must contain at least one element.

data.name: InconsistentEntityType
data.value: The properties provided for the argument '{argumentName}' are declared on different entity types.

data.name: EntityRequiresKey
data.value: The entity type '{entityType}' requires a key to be defined.

data.name: KeyPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified key properties {key} are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure key properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: ForeignKeyPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified foreign key properties {foreignKey} are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure foreign key properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: IndexPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified index properties {index} are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure index properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: IQueryableNotAsync
data.value: The source IQueryable doesn't implement IAsyncEnumerable<{genericParameter}>. Only sources that implement IAsyncEnumerable can be used for Entity Framework asynchronous operations.

data.name: IQueryableProviderNotAsync
data.value: The provider for the source IQueryable doesn't implement IAsyncQueryProvider. Only providers that implement IEntityQueryProvider can be used for Entity Framework asynchronous operations.

data.name: EagerOriginalValuesRequired
data.value: Lazy original value tracking cannot be turned on for entity type '{entityType}'. Entities that do not implement both INotifyPropertyChanging and INotifyPropertyChanged require original values to be stored eagerly in order to correct detect changes made to entities.

data.name: OriginalValueNotTracked
data.value: The original value for property '{property}' of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be accessed because it is not being tracked. To access all original values set 'UseLazyOriginalValues' to false on the entity type.

data.name: MissingBackingField
data.value: The property '{entityType}.{property}' is annotated with backing field '{field}' but that field cannot be found.

data.name: BadBackingFieldType
data.value: The annotated backing field '{field}' of type '{fieldType}' cannot be used for the property '{entityType}.{property}' of type '{propertyType}'. Only backing fields of types that are assignable from the property type can be used.

data.name: NoFieldOrSetter
data.value: No backing field could be discovered for property '{entityType}.{property}' and the property does not have a setter. Either use a backing field name that can be matched by convention, annotate the property with a backing field, or define a property setter.

data.name: NoClrType
data.value: The CLR entity materializer cannot be used for entity type '{entityType}' because it is a shadow-state entity type. Materialization to a CLR type is only possible for entity types that have a corresponding CLR type.

data.name: MultipleProvidersConfigured
data.value: The database providers {storeNames}are configured. A context can only be configured to use a single database provider.

data.name: NoProviderConfigured
data.value: No database providers are configured. Configure a database provider by overriding OnConfiguring in your DbContext class or in the AddDbContext method when setting up services.

data.name: NoProviderServices
data.value: No database providers are available. Ensure that database provider services are added inside the call to AddEntityFramework on your ServiceCollection.

data.name: MultipleProvidersAvailable
data.value: The database providers {storeNames}are available. A context can only be configured to use a single database provider. Configure a database provider by overriding OnConfiguring in your DbContext class or in the AddDbContext method when setting up services.

data.name: NoValueGenerator
data.value: The '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' does not have a value set and no value generator is available for properties of type '{propertyType}'. Either set a value for the property before adding the entity or configure a value generator for properties of type '{propertyType}'.

data.name: TempValuePersists
data.value: The property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' has a temporary value while attempting to change the entity's state to '{state}'. Either set a permanent value explicitly or ensure that the database is configured to generate values for this property.

data.name: LogExceptionDuringQueryIteration
data.value: An exception occurred in the database while iterating the results of a query.{newline}{error}

data.name: LogExceptionDuringSaveChanges
data.value: An exception occurred in the database while saving changes.{newline}{error}

data.name: PropertyMethodInvoked
data.value: The EF.Property<T> method may only be used within LINQ queries.

data.name: DuplicateProperty

data.name: NoClrProperty
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot exist on entity type '{entityType}' because the property is not marked as shadow state and no corresponding CLR property exists on the underlying type.

data.name: PropertyWrongClrType

data.name: ClrPropertyOnShadowEntity
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot exist on entity type '{entityType}' because the entity type is marked as shadow state while the property is not. Shadow state entity types can only contain shadow state properties.

data.name: PropertyInUse
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot be removed from entity type '{entityType}' because it is being used in an index or key. All indexes and keys must be removed or redefined before the property can be removed.

data.name: KeyInUse
data.value: Cannot remove key {key} from entity type '{entityType}' because it is referenced by a foreign key in entity type '{dependentType}'. All foreign keys must be removed or redefined before the referenced key can be removed.

data.name: DuplicateNavigation
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because a navigation property with the same name already exists on entity type '{duplicateEntityType}'.

data.name: NavigationOnShadowEntity

data.name: NavigationSingleWrongClrType

data.name: NavigationCollectionWrongClrType
data.value: The collection navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because its CLR type '{clrType}' does not implement 'IEnumerable<{targetType}>'. Collection navigation properties must implement IEnumerable<> of the related entity.

data.name: ForeignKeyCountMismatch
data.value: The number of properties specified for the foreign key {foreignKey} on entity type '{dependentType}' does not match the number of properties in the principal key {principalKey} on entity type '{principalType}'.

data.name: ForeignKeyTypeMismatch

data.name: NavigationBadType

data.name: NavigationNoGetter

data.name: NavigationNoSetter

data.name: NavigationCannotCreateType
data.value: The type of navigation property '{navigation}' on the entity type '{entityType}' is '{foundType}' for which it was not possible to create a concrete instance. Either initialize the property before use, add a public parameterless constructor to the type, or use a type which can be assigned a HashSet<> or List<>.

data.name: KeyReadOnly

data.name: PropertyReadOnlyAfterSave

data.name: PropertyReadOnlyBeforeSave

data.name: KeyPropertyMustBeReadOnly
data.value: The property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' must be marked as read-only after it has been saved because it is part of a key. Key properties are always read-only once an entity has been saved for the first time.

data.name: RelationshipConceptualNull

data.name: PropertyConceptualNull
